  "title": "Pronouncing the Plural 'S'",
  "learningGoal": "The learner will master the three distinct phonetic sounds of the English plural (-s / -z / -iz) dependent on the origin word's final consonant.",
  "difficultyLevel": "beginner",
  "baseLanguage": "hi",
  "targetLanguage": "en",
  "estimatedTime": 45,
  "prerequisites": ["en_hi_M1B3_lesson_001"],
  "instructions": "In English, adding 's' to the end of a word makes 3 different sounds depending on the word. Sometimes it sounds like a snake 'S' (स). Sometimes it buzzes like a bee 'Z' (ज़). Sometimes it adds a whole new syllable 'IZ' (इज़). Listen closely and repeat these 15 words.",
  "contentItems": [
    {
      "type": "note",
      "text": "Do not pronounce every 's' like 'स'. 'Dogs' MUST buzz. It is 'Dogg-z', not 'Dogg-s'."
    }
  ],
